race.comment: CEEKAY'S CHOICE (1) is unlucky to still be a maiden placing in four of six overall and this is not an overly strong affair. Strips fitter second-up from the break and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. Will prove very hard to toss. MISSISSIPPI DREAM (6) was okay in town on debut before being tipped out for further time to furnish. Tuned up for this with a recent trial placing and must be respected from the Vandyke barn. Expect a forward showing while fresh. HURRICANE LU (2) is facing the starter for the first time but has shown ability at the trials and any market support must be noted. YAKITORI (9) will be ready to peak now third-up and may earn some minor money. ACCESSORIZED (7) next best.
